# Alessa: Compliance and Fraud Detection Simplified

## Overview and Origin

* Name of company
**CaseWare RCM** < https://www.caseware.com/alessa/>
CaseWare RCM is a RegTech company whose flagship is Alessa, a software solution. 

* When was the company incorporated?
CaseWare RCM was incorporated in Canada in 2006.
In 2019, CaeWare RCM rebranded its continuous control monitoring program as Alessa.
Alessa software is used in the United States, Canada, UK, Germany, Australia, Caribbean, Latin America, Asia, Kenya. 

* Who are the founders of the company?
CaseWare RCM is a division of CaseWare International <https://www.caseware.com>
Caseware International is a firm that develops software solutions for accounting, auditing, financial, risk and governance professionals. CaseWare software is used in 130 countries and available in 16 languages.

* How did the idea for the company (or project) come about?
According to Andrew Simpson, COO, the original Continuous Control Monitoring (CCM) focus was on leveraging data analytics to automate internal auditors' role. Compliance departments primarily used the software; therefore, this was the area where CaseWare RCM extended their capabilities to include customer due diligence, transaction monitoring, and regulatory reporting to financial intelligence units.

* How is the company funded? How much funding have they received?
CaseWare RCM is a division of CaseWare International.

## Business Activities:

* What specific financial problem is the company or project trying to solve?
Alessa seeks to quickly identify suspicious transactions and high-risk entities in compliance, finance, purchasing, and procurement programs. Early detection of high risks enables organizations to start timely investigations, make informed decisions, automatically create an auditable trail, comply with regulations and protect revenues.
Alessa tracks activities and transactions across corporate purchases and credit cards to detect anomalies, personal purchases, policy violations and other misuses. Using the sanctions screening module makes possible to conduct on-demand, periodic, or real-time screening to evaluate and remediate risks. Additionally, the regulatory reporting tools enable regulators to auto-populate, validate and electronically submit currency transactions, suspicious activity and suspicious transaction reports.

* Who is the company's intended customer? Is there any information about the market size of this set of customers?
The main customers of CaseWare RCM and Alessa's intended users are banks, money service businesses, fintech, insurance, gaming, manufacturing and retail companies.

* What solution does this company offer that their competitors do not or cannot offer? (What is the unfair advantage they utilize?)
Alessa offers a comprehensive solution that includes all critical functions to comply with anti-money laundering and counter terrorist financing regulations, such as identity verification, due diligence, sanctions and watch list screening, transaction monitoring, transaction screening, and regulatory reporting capabilities.
Thanks to its application programming interface (API), Alessa fully integrates with several third-party solutions, as well as it has the ability to integrate data from disparate IT and business systems. In this sense, clients can fully view the data in their organization, use this information, and take a risk-based approach to their AML/CTF program.
Alessa features include: Compliance tracking, behavioural analytics, compliance reporting, investigation management, transactions monitoring, case management, identity verification, PEP screening, suspicious transactions/activities reports, watchlist, risk management, check fraud detection, customer account profiles, internal fraud monitoring, custom fraud rules, data mining, financial fraud detection for banking and the insurance industry. 

* Which technologies are they currently using, and how are they implementing them? (This may take a little bit of sleuthing–– you may want to search the company's engineering blog or use sites like Stackshare to find this information.)
Alessa's technology partners include CipherTrace, Micorsoft Azure, Refinitive (World-Check) and Thomson Reuters.
In September 2020, CaseWare RCM announced its partnership with CipherTrace. The partnership was established to "allow financial institutions (FIs)to more effectively track the accounts associated with peer-to-peer crypto exchanges and smaller virtual currency kiosks, and cross-references the contact information of small virtual asset service providers (VASPs) with customer records to flag suspicious activities." 
In terms of customer identification and due diligence capabilities, Alessa customers enjoy the benefits of third-party data and risk intelligence, provided by Refinitiv World-Check and EDD reports, Thomson Reuters CLEAR ID Confirm™, Dow Jones Risk & Compliance, and cannabis-related data.

Additionally, and according to Crunchbase, CaseWare RCM is actively using 27 technologies for its website. These include Viewport Meta, IPhone / Mobile Compatible, and Apple Mobile Web Clips Icon.

Additionally, in Stackshare it is possible to find information about Caseware, however it does not clarify whether it refers to CaseWare International or CaseWare RCM.
